			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I think the core message is good. Bitcoin doesn&#039;t behave like a currency. Not even really like a commodity &#8212; more like a collectable, by design. It shouldn&#039;t surprise anyone that the bitcoin market then acts more like the market in Beanie Babies and less like the market in gold or flax. </p>
<p>I think the call for regulation is a little off-point, though. While any market might or might not need regulation, bitcoin&#039;s has especially undesirable features that call out for it. An alternative currency that was designed with more desirable properties would have less need of regulation. </p>
