	<li id="comment-20028" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
		<article id="div-comment-20028" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
					<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/a3b6865cb0833158fe164f2dda96bb7f?s=75&amp;d=retro&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-75 photo' height='75' width='75' />					<cite class="fn"><a href="http://www.technollama.co.uk/"   rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Andres</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<a href="http://www.technollama.co.uk/we-need-decentralized-cryptocurrencies-we-just-dont-need-bitcoin/comment-page-1#comment-20028">
						<time datetime="2013-04-12T21:54:00+00:00">
							April 12, 2013 at 9:54 pm						</time>
					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Just one comment about the huge <a href="http://blockchain.info/tx/5d9ef693d41cb3bb4c6d98e70ea8b2cc91be29a804245a06ec8761d9cddc103c" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-comment','http://blockchain.info']);" rel="nofollow">69k BTC transaction</a>. It is now clear that this did not cause the crash, it took place the day before, just before the trades that led to the big price drop. Looking at it closely, it is more likely that this is the result of a large holder amassing funds in a single address, as it originates from two addresses, one holding <a href="http://blockchain.info/address/1BADznNF3W1gi47R65MQs754KB7zTaGuYZ" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-comment','http://blockchain.info']);" rel="nofollow">22.8k BTC</a> and one holding <a href="http://blockchain.info/address/1BBqjKsYuLEUE9Y5WzdbzCtYzCiQgHqtPN" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-comment','http://blockchain.info']);" rel="nofollow">47.5k BTC</a>. We know that the 69k haven&#039;t moved from the receiving address, and we also know that it did not cause the crash because a 69k single transaction would wipe out the value of Bitcoin in one go given the volumes at Mt.Gox and other exchanges. </p>
<p>However, the point stands. This is a market where early adopters have hundreds of thousands of coins, they can wipe the market at one go. The system is stacked too much in favour of the large holder, how could anyone invest knowing these figures? </p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

