	<li id="comment-20284" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
		<article id="div-comment-20284" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
					<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d3dc44ba920d254942eded0b6acf12c4?s=75&amp;d=retro&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-75 photo' height='75' width='75' />					<cite class="fn">Mark Jumaga</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<a href="http://www.technollama.co.uk/we-need-decentralized-cryptocurrencies-we-just-dont-need-bitcoin/comment-page-1#comment-20284">
						<time datetime="2014-01-02T22:13:45+00:00">
							January 2, 2014 at 10:13 pm						</time>
					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Ok, I&#8217;ll bite.<br />
This article is completely useless in describing the value of crypto currency. It describes the world except bitcoin and alternate crypto currencies. Here are some facts about crypto currency :<br />
1) They are a new paradigm. NOBODY has seen a bitcoin before. Describing bitcoin using old paradigm&#8217;s is completely useless.<br />
2) Bitcoins are exactly like the US dollar in that US dollars are also purchased and have value in other currencies.<br />
3) Crypto currencies with the same support infrastructure are exactly the same as bitcoin for the purposes of this discussion. In other words, Litecoin=bitcoin=junkcoin. Yes, they have small algorithmic differences, but they are all peer to peer decentralized currencies. From here on in I&#8217;ll use the term bitcoin to mean all crypto currencies.<br />
4) Crypto currencies have tremendous value: a) They are free from manipulation by a central bank. Look at the pathetic way the dollar has been devalued by the federal reserve : 3 trillion dollars in the last year alone of printing money. b) They are worldwide, there is no political barrier to a crypto currency. If I want to buy a Yak in tibet I can do that without anyone else involved. All I need is the market. c) They are backed by a transaction register. Frankly, if someone wanted to steal bitcoin the ledger would describe EXACTLY where the coin went &#8211; if to another crypto currency ledger then add up all the crypto currency ledgers to determine the trail. If to a fiat currency bank then you know exactly where it exited the system and who owned the account.<br />
WHO says they don&#8217;t have value?<br />
5) Discussions about the dollar value of bitcoin vs. price stability is the dumbest thing I have ever heard of. The dollar has a value that fluctuates just like a bitcoin. What&#8217;s the difference? The difference is that a bitcoin is brand new, the infrastructure is brand new, the investments are brand new. What happens when you drop a boulder in a lake? The waves are large and violent until the energy of the introduction dissipates into the surrounding system. The cryptocurrency market as a whole is ONLY INCREASING in value, regardless of the price of a specific instrument. Once the market is a trillion dollars, the price fluctuations from individual transactions, whether hoarding or selling, will be un-discernible. If you want to argue the point, please defend the position that NO ONE in the world will want to spend money. </p>
<p>Cryto currencies are the tip of an engineered financial system iceberg that is going to change the world. Each cryptocoin comes with the ability to loosely engineer the transaction. This means social engineering by voting with which cryptocurrency I use to make a transaction. It&#8217;s called DEMOCRACY.<br />
The filth that runs the fiat loan slave backing system in the world today has already lost the battle, they just don&#8217;t know it yet.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

